Stuff'd, as they say, with honourable parts,
Look to't, think on't; I do not use to jest.
Thursday is near; lay hand on heart, advise:
I think it best you married with the County.
Romeo's a dishclout to him. An eagle, madam,
Thou and my bosom henceforth shall be twain.
Paris. God shield I should disturb devotion!
Therefore, out of thy long-experienc'd time,
As that is desperate which we would prevent.
A thing like death to chide away this shame,
Like death when he shuts up the day of life;
Cap. So many guests invite as here are writ.
What, is my daughter gone to Friar Laurence?
They are all forth; well, I will walk myself
Where bloody Tybalt, yet but green in earth,
So early waking- what with loathsome smells,
As with a club dash out my desp'rate brains?
But I will watch you from such watching now.
The County will be here with music straight,
Ties up my tongue and will not let me speak.
O love! O life! not life, but love in death!
O child! O child! my soul, and not my child!
Our bridal flowers serve for a buried corse;
1. Mus. An you re us and fa us, you note us.
With speedy help doth lend redress.' [Exit.]
1. Mus. What a pestilent knave is this same?
Well, Juliet, I will lie with thee to-night.
And hereabouts 'a dwells, which late I noted
And fearest to die? Famine is in thy cheeks,
Apoth. Put this in any liquid thing you will
Farewell. Buy food and get thyself in flesh.
Friar J. Holy Franciscan Friar, Brother, ho!
Or, if his mind be writ, give me his letter.
So that my speed to Mantua there was stay'd.
Friar L. Who bare my letter, then, to Romeo?
Friar L. Unhappy fortune! By my brotherhood,
The letter was not nice, but full of charge,
Give me those flowers. Do as I bid thee, go.
Hold, take this letter. Early in the morning
Gorg'd with the dearest morsel of the earth,
Can vengeance be pursu'd further than death?
He told me Paris should have married Juliet.
And death's pale flag is not advanced there.
For fear of that I still will stay with thee
Come, bitter conduct; come, unsavoury guide!
We see the ground whereon these woes do lie,
Enter another Whatchman with FRIAR LAURENCE.
We took this mattock and this spade from him
That calls our person from our morning rest?
What further woe conspires against mine age?
You, to remove that siege of grief from her,
To help to take her from her borrowed grave,
Came I to take her from her kindred's vault;
But then a noise did scare me from the tomb,
This letter he early bid me give his father,
Sirrah, what made your master in this place?
Samp. I mean, an we be in choler, we'll draw.
Put up your swords. You know not what you do.
then enter three or four CITIZENS with clubs.
Ben. Here were the servants of your adversary
And yours, close fighting ere I did approach.
Till the Prince came, who parted either part.
Ben. Madam, an hour before the worshipp'd sun
Mont. Many a morning hath he there been seen,
Ere he can spread his sweet leaves to the air
To hear true shrift. Come, madam, let's away.
Should without eyes see pathways to his will!
In penalty alike; and 'tis not hard, I think,
Cap. But saying o'er what I have said before:
One more, most welcome, makes my number more.
Which, on more view of many, mine, being one,
Compare her face with some that I shall show,
Susan and she (God rest all Christian souls!)
On Lammas Eve at night shall she be fourteen;
And she was wean'd (I never shall forget it),
The pretty wretch left crying, and said 'Ay.'
To think it should leave crying and say 'Ay.'
This night you shall behold him at our feast.
Romeo. I am too sore enpierced with his shaft
To soar with his light feathers; and so bound
Here are the beetle brows shall blush for me.
Tickle the senseless rushes with their heels;
Five times in that ere once in our five wits.
Her wagon spokes made of long spinners' legs,
Her collars, of the moonshine's wat'ry beams;
And in this state she 'gallops night by night
Cap. Content thee, gentle coz, let him alone.
Well said, my hearts!- You are a princox- go!
Now seeming sweet, convert to bitt'rest gall.
I nurs'd her daughter that you talk'd withal.
Ben. Away, be gone; the sport is at the best.
Come, let's away; the strangers all are gone.
And, on my life, hath stol'n him home to bed.
Ben. An if he hear thee, thou wilt anger him.
Mer. This cannot anger him. 'Twould anger him
And wish his mistress were that kind of fruit
'To seek him here that means not to be found.
To twinkle in their spheres till they return.
The orchard walls are high and hard to climb,
Dost thou love me, I know thou wilt say 'Ay';
Thou mayst prove false. At lovers' perjuries,
But trust me, gentleman, I'll prove more true
Romeo. O blessed, blessed night! I am afeard,
Thy purpose marriage, send me word to-morrow,
And follow thee my lord throughout the world.
Romeo. It is my soul that calls upon my name.
The day to cheer and night's dank dew to dry,
The earth that's nature's mother is her tomb.
But to the earth some special good doth give;
In man as well as herbs- grace and rude will;
I have forgot that name, and that name's woe.
And all combin'd, save what thou must combine
Not truly in their hearts, but in their eyes.
The sun not yet thy sighs from heaven clears,
Thy old groans ring yet in mine ancient ears.
Doth grace for grace and love for love allow.
immortal passado! the punto reverse! the hay.
