Therefore do nimble-pinion'd doves draw Love,
Nurse. Peter, stay at the gate. [Exit PETER.]
If good, thou shamest the music of sweet news
Where should she be? How oddly thou repliest!
Now comes the wanton blood up in your cheeks:
But you shall bear the burthen soon at night.
Therefore love moderately: long love doth so;
For, by your leaves, you shall not stay alone
Ben. We talk here in the public haunt of men.
No better term than this: thou art a villain.
Tybalt under Romeo's arm thrusts Mercutio in.
Romeo. Courage, man. The hurt cannot be much.
That late thou gavest me; for Mercutio's soul
Of my dear kinsman! Prince, as thou art true,
Prince. Benvolio, who began this bloody fray?
Who, all as hot, turns deadly point to point,
And all those twenty could but kill one life.
Who now the price of his dear blood doth owe?
I have an interest in your hate's proceeding,
Therefore use none. Let Romeo hence in haste,
Mercy but murders, pardoning those that kill.
It best agrees with night. Come, civil night,
That all the world will be in love with night
[Enter NURSE with cords, wringing her hands.]
Nurse. Ay, ay, the cords. [Throws them down.]
This torture should be roar'd in dismal hell.
Or those eyes shut that make thee answer 'I.'
Vile earth, to earth resign; end motion here,
For 'tis a throne where honour may be crown'd
But with a rearward following Tybalt's death,
Friar L. Hence from Verona art thou banished.
And world's exile is death. Then 'banishment'
Friar L. O deadly sin! O rude unthankfulness!
This may flies do, when I from this must fly;
Where is she? and how doth she! and what says
And now falls on her bed, and then starts up,
There art thou happy. Tybalt would kill thee,
Take heed, take heed, for such die miserable.
But look thou stay not till the watch be set,
Where thou shalt live till we can find a time
Of my child's love. I think she will be rul'd
And bid her (mark you me?) on Wednesday next-
That pierc'd the fearful hollow of thine ear.
Night's candles are burnt out, and jocund day
Come, death, and welcome! Juliet wills it so.
How is't, my soul? Let's talk; it is not day.
Since arm from arm that voice doth us affray,
Hunting thee hence with hunt's-up to the day!
Shall happily make thee there a joyful bride.
For still thy eyes, which I may call the sea,
Good Prudence. Smatter with your gossips, go!
For, by my soul, I'll ne'er acknowledge thee,
Your first is dead- or 'twere as good he were
Or to dispraise my lord with that same tongue
Which she hath prais'd him with above compare
Juliet. If I do so, it will be of more price,
Juliet. It may be so, for it is not mine own.
And ere this hand, by thee to Romeo's seal'd,
With reeky shanks and yellow chapless skulls;
Shall keep his native progress, but surcease;
And in this borrowed likeness of shrunk death
Now, when the bridegroom in the morning comes
In this resolve. I'll send a friar with speed
Lady Cap. We shall be short in our provision.
Since this same wayward girl is so reclaim'd.
And let the nurse this night sit up with you;
No, No! This shall forbid it. Lie thou there.
I fear it is; and yet methinks it should not,
[She falls upon her bed within the curtains.]
