And therefore thou mayst think my haviour light;
Than those that have more cunning to be strange.
I should have been more strange, I must confess,
That tips with silver all these fruit-tree tops-
Good night, good night! As sweet repose and rest
How silver-sweet sound lovers' tongues by night,
If e'er thou wast thyself, and these woes thine,
Friar L. For doting, not for loving, pupil mine.
Thy love did read by rote, that could not spell.
Romeo. O, let us hence! I stand on sudden haste.
Mer. Any man that can write may answer a letter.
Ben. Thou wouldst else have made thy tale large.
Of this day's journey, and from nine till twelve
My back o' t' other side,- ah, my back, my back!
Friar L. So smile the heavens upon this holy act
Which, as they kiss, consume. The sweetest honey
They are but beggars that can count their worth;
That thou hast done me; therefore turn and draw.
Could draw to part them, was stout Tybalt slain;
Some twenty of them fought in this black strife,
His fault concludes but what the law should end,
Nor tears nor prayers shall purchase out abuses.
Spread thy close curtain, love-performing night,
Nurse. I saw the wound, I saw it with mine eyes,
Back, foolish tears, back to your native spring!
Some word there was, worser than Tybalt's death,
Why followed not, when she said 'Tybalt's dead,'
Romeo. Ha, banishment? Be merciful, say 'death';
Friar L. O, then I see that madmen have no ears.
Friar L. Let me dispute with thee of thy estate.
For Juliet's sake, for her sake, rise and stand!
Romeo. Do so, and bid my sweet prepare to chide.
Paris. These times of woe afford no tune to woo.
In all respects by me; nay more, I doubt it not.
No nightingale. Look, love, what envious streaks
Therefore stay yet; thou need'st not to be gone.
Some say the lark and loathed toad chang'd eyes;
Juliet. Yet let me weep for such a feeling loss.
As that the villain lives which slaughter'd him.
Cap. When the sun sets the air doth drizzle dew,
Do ebb and flow with tears; the bark thy body is
How? Will she none? Doth she not give us thanks?
Juliet. To answer that, I should confess to you.
Being spoke behind your back, than to your face.
God join'd my heart and Romeo's, thou our hands;
That cop'st with death himself to scape from it;
Juliet. O, bid me leap, rather than marry Paris,
Where serpents are; chain me with roaring bears,
No warmth, no breath, shall testify thou livest;
To rouse thee from thy bed, there art thou dead.
Cap. Well, be may chance to do some good on her.
Juliet. Where I have learnt me to repent the sin
I'll play the housewife for this once. What, ho!
All night for lesser cause, and ne'er been sick.
Why, love, I say! madam! sweetheart! Why, bride!
What, not a word? You take your pennyworths now!
Sleep for a week; for the next night, I warrant,
And leave him all. Life, living, all is Death's.
Had part in this fair maid! now heaven hath all,
